<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> risk capital • risk money</xh5><p> <i>risk capital</i>—(also: venture capital) money for speculative business investment: Kula Fund was established to provide long-term <u>risk capital</u> to private sector projects in the Pacific. </p><p><i>risk money—</i>1. allowance to a cashier to compensate for ordinary errors: To meet deficiencies, some banks allow to each cashier a certain sum, which is called <u>risk-money</u>. 2. <i>= risk capital: </i>A business man ought to be able to get his “<u>risk money</u>” back before he has to pay too much in the way of taxation.</p> </entry>
